HEADWORD: Anaglyptograph
<hw>An`a*glyp"to*graph</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
+ <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument by which a correct
engraving of any embossed object, such as a medal or cameo, can be
executed.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

